<p class="indent0" style="-uslm-lc:I11" xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">Tax liability incurred to the Virgin Islands pursuant to this subtitle, as made applicable in the Virgin Islands by the Act entitled “An Act making appropriations for the naval service for the fiscal year ending <date date="1922-06-30">June 30, 1922</date>, and for other purposes”, approved <date date="1921-07-12">July 12, 1921</date> (<ref href="/us/usc/t48/s1397">48 U.S.C. 1397</ref>), or pursuant to section 28(a) of the Revised Organic Act of the Virgin Islands, approved <date date="1954-07-22">July 22, 1954</date> (<ref href="/us/usc/t48/s1642">48 U.S.C. 1642</ref>), shall not be reduced or remitted in any way, directly or indirectly, whether by grant, subsidy, or other similar payment, by any law enacted in the Virgin Islands, except to the extent provided in subsection (b).</p>
